message.body: How's summer been?
sorta lonely, but good. i'm in nc at the beach at the moment. and youuu?
Pretty good. Been working a lot but other than that getting some relaxation and needed best friend time in
sounds good. are you delivering for pepsi or whatever it was again?
Yup delivering soda. Almost everyday
must be a good workout. are you rowing at all?
It is a decent workout Rowing recreationally. I got dragged back into competitive frisbee and am spending a lot of time with that. And just going to the gym
"dragged back", haha, so torturous, poor you...
I didn't really keep my heels dug in haha
who are you playing with? just like a casual thing?
A pick-up group in a near-by town and I got recruited to go play at a tournament in wildwood
fancy! you're going pro. :)
Haha if anything it's semi-pro but yeah we'll see if I can make a splash. Get it because wildwood is a beach town
ha i didn't get it but now i do. do you think you'll keep playing back at emory?
Yeah I quit crew. So I'm gonna need some sport. I liked juice (the men's ultimate team) the semester I was on it
why is it called that?!
Juice? Idk why is the women's ultimate team called Luna?
luna is a cute name. juice is kinda gross...
But the shirts look so cool. And the logo is like an orange with a straw sticking out
that makes it less gross, i guess...
There are also much worse options like moist
Or more gross worse
*words
sports do make you moist... like in a sweaty way. still super gross, though.
Does frisbee make us juicy? Because I don't think that was what the namer was thinking about...
ew, no, stop talking
I wasn't I was texting
texting is more like speech than writing, you know that
Canon referred to me as one of her favorite students when I met her son and daughter.
i emailed her that ted talk i snapchatted you and she was sooo sweet in her reply. she must not have hated us as much as we thought.
I mean we participated and were engaged. Just sometimes too much so
that's a really nice way of saying it, hahaha.
Haha of course. I'm representing the LaurenandZachcentric viewpoint
aka the best and only viewpoint
